  h1 msrd
    span .io

  p.slug microsoft regional directors 

  :markdown
    The Microsoft Regional Director program has a new logo. In keeping with the 
    spirit of Microsoft's 2012 corporate and product line rebranding, the RD 
    logo was refashioned to reflect their new design asthetic:

  ul
    li Monochromatic
    li Segoe typeface
    li Simple layout and icon
    li Semantic HTML

  h2 The Logo
  p.
    There are three sizes of images (all PNGs) to choose from, with each size
    coming in 2 flavors: white background and transparent background.

  ul
    li 336 x 96 pixels
    li 672 x 192 pixels
    li 1344 x 384 pixels

  h3 Small

  figure
    a(href='/logo/msrd-logo-96px.png')
      img(src='/logo/msrd-logo-96px.png', alt='logo 96 pixels', width=336, height=96)
    figcaption 336x96 px png

  figure
    a(href='/logo/msrd-logo-96px-alpha.png')
      img(src='/logo/msrd-logo-96px-alpha.png', width=336, height=96)
    figcaption 336x96 px with alpha transparency png

  h3 Medium

  figure
    a(href='/logo/msrd-logo-192px.png')
      img(src='/logo/msrd-logo-192px.png', width=672, height=192)
    figcaption 672x192 pixel png

  h3 Large

  :markdown
    The really big version of the logo is 1344 x 384 pixels, available in 
    [white](/logo/msrd-logo-384px.png) or 
    [transparent](/logo/msrd-logo-384px-alpha.png) backgrounds. 

  h2 Details

  p.
    Compare the new logo with the previous version, which was in use for the
    past decade. It featured the as-of-then corporate typeface with a narrow
    band of the four primary Microsoft colors. 

  figure
    a(href='/logo/msrd-old-96px.jpg')
      img(src='/logo/msrd-old-96px.jpg', width=212, height=96)
    figcaption rd logo prior to 2013

  :markdown
      Then contrast the new logo within the larger Microsoft [product family like Office and Xbox](http://www.neowin.net/news/the-new-microsoft-brand-family-at-a-glance).

  p More details about the logo files
    ul
      li Rendered from Adobe Illustrator 
      li File size minimized and optimized with <a href='http://optipng.sourceforge.net'>OptiPNG</a>
      li Image height is evenly divisble by 16 or 24 pixels for typographical baseline
      li The logo is a 3 Â½ : 1 ratio  
      li The screen color is <span class="invert">rgb (9, 79, 178)</span>
      li For print, use <span class="invert">cmyk (85, 50, 0, 0)</span>
      li.
         Designed by Sean Dolinsky at <a href="http://www.vertigo.com">Vertigo</a>. 
         Some of his <a href='logo/sketches.png'>early sketches</a>.

  :markdown
    Explore the source code at [github](http://github.com/msrd/msrd.io).

